    <title>Algorithm Training for the Interview</title>
    <url>/interview/</url>
    <content><![CDATA[<h1 id="Personal-Introduction"><a href="#Personal-Introduction" class="headerlink" title="Personal Introduction"></a>Personal Introduction</h1><p>I was born and grew up in China, I went to the university in 2014 and finished it in 2018, studying programming for 4 years. After devoting 10k+ hours, I finished over 4~5k programming problems with record.</p>
<p>During college, I won the bronze, silver, and gold medals from freshman to junior year respectively. And went to the ICPC World Finals (International Collegiate Programming Contest).</p>
<p>I passed almost all of my interviews (Alibaba, Baidu, Bytedance, Huawei, etc.) and went to Microsoft after graduation. Then got a change to Google Tokyo.</p>
<p>I think algorithm programming skill is one of the reasons I could pass many interviews easily. There are many ingenious problems and skills to share. Welcome to the algorithm programming world! As someone with a dream of becoming an algorithm teacher, I will be glad to help :D~</p>
